-- South African Richards Bay Coal Price at 19-Month Low
-- B y   R o b   V e r d o n c k
-- 2012-05-15T14:27:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/south-african-richards-bay-coal-price-at-19-month-low.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
Richards Bay, the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, fell for a fifth week.  Prices declined 16 cents, or 0.2 percent, to $97.21 a
metric ton in the week ended May 11, according to IHS McCloskey
data on Bloomberg. That’s the lowest level since Oct. 29, 2010.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Verdonck in London at 
